Chalo bhai, EFS (Elastic File System) ko EKS pe persistent storage ke liye setup karte hain step-by-step in Hinglish, real DevOps style 🚀

🧠 Concept samajh le pehle
Amazon EKS = managed Kubernetes
Amazon EFS = shared storage (NFS based)

👉 EFS = multiple pods across nodes ek hi storage share kar sakte hain
👉 Perfect for: logs, shared files, CMS, ML workloads

🔥 Step-by-Step Setup
🔹 1. EFS Create karo
AWS Console → EFS → Create
Important config:
VPC = same as EKS
Subnets = all AZs (high availability)
Security Group:
Allow inbound NFS (2049) from EKS nodes SG
🔹 2. IAM Role (IRSA) setup

👉 EKS ko permission chahiye EFS access karne ke liye

Create IAM policy:

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Action": [
        "elasticfilesystem:DescribeAccessPoints",
        "elasticfilesystem:DescribeFileSystems"
      ],
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}

👉 Attach this to Service Account using IRSA

🔹 3. EFS CSI Driver install karo

👉 Ye driver EKS ko EFS mount karne deta hai

kubectl apply -k "github.com/kubernetes-sigs/aws-efs-csi-driver/deploy/kubernetes/overlays/stable"

👉 Verify:

kubectl get pods -n kube-system
🔹 4. StorageClass create karo
apiVersion: storage.k8s.io/v1
kind: StorageClass
metadata:
  name: efs-sc
provisioner: efs.csi.aws.com
parameters:
  provisioningMode: efs-ap
  fileSystemId: <EFS-ID>
  directoryPerms: "700"

Apply:

kubectl apply -f sc.yaml
🔹 5. PersistentVolumeClaim (PVC)
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: efs-pvc
spec:
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteMany     # 🔥 multi pod access
  storageClassName: efs-sc
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: 5Gi

Apply:

kubectl apply -f pvc.yaml
🔹 6. Pod / Deployment use karo
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: efs-app
spec:
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: nginx
    volumeMounts:
    - mountPath: /data
      name: efs-volume
  volumes:
  - name: efs-volume
    persistentVolumeClaim:
      claimName: efs-pvc

👉 /data = shared storage (same across pods)

🔥 Real Production Flow
Pod A writes file → /data/file.txt
Pod B (different node) reads same file ✅
👉 That’s power of EFS (RWX mode)
⚠️ Common Issues (Interview Gold 💣)
❌ 1. Pod stuck in Pending

👉 Check:

kubectl describe pvc
❌ 2. Mount failed

👉 Check:

Security group (port 2049 open?)
EFS in same VPC?
❌ 3. Permission issue

👉 Fix:

directoryPerms: "777"
🧠 Easy Memory Trick
EBS → single pod (RWO)
EFS → multiple pods (RWX) 🔥
🚀 Real Interview Line

👉 “In production EKS, we use EFS with CSI driver and RWX PVC to enable shared storage across pods for stateful workloads.”
